 Actor Amber Heard arrives in the courtroom at the Fairfax County Circuit Court in Fairfax, Va., Thursday, April 28, 2022. Actor Johnny Depp sued his ex-wife actor Amber Heard for libel in Fairfax County Circuit Court after she wrote an op-ed piece in The Washington Post in 2018 referring to herself as a “public figure representing domestic abuse.” (Michael Reynolds/Pool Photo via AP) Amber Heard has employed a new team led by David Shane before she takes the stand this week in hopes of a good testimony on her side. Amber Heard fired her previous PR team after a series of bad headlines about the defamation trial in the past weeks. The actress’s decision to let her previous PR team happens shortly days she has been scheduled to take the stand in court. According to a source, the Amber Heard has been upset about the bad headlines making the news since the trial commenced. Some sources said ‘‘She doesn’t like bad headlines.” Another source confirmed that the Aquaman actress is “frustrated with her story not being told effectively.” The defamation trial began with Depp, suing Heard for $50 million, based on an article that defamed him as an abuser. However, Heard’s team have defended the actress alleging that she was sexually and physically abused by Depp who in turn denies these allegations. Amber Heard who has not taken the stand since the inception of the trial is expected to take the stand in Fairfax, Va on Tuesday. With a new PR team on the ground, they hope to help her get her side of the story to be better told in court. Since the ongoing trial fans have expressed their rage at the actress and even signed a petition of over 2 million signatures to get her off the sequel of Aquaman.